<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-21"><hi rend="italic">April 21, 1895</hi></date>.
                                (Received May 6.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 511.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge your No.
                            414, of the 8th instant, regarding the visit of the <hi rend="italic">San Francisco</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> to Turkish
                            waters. The arrival of the former at Sagua was attended with the usual
                            courtesies, and must tend to promote cordial relations.</p>
                        <p>I answered the inquiry of the Porte on the subject that the visit of the
                                <hi rend="italic">San Francisco</hi> was a friendly one, but such
                            vessels were designed for the protection of American interests.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>